I know that some cats do enjoy or at least tolerate traveling in a carrier
in a car. I have never had a cat like that. They always go to their
&quot;mountain lion&quot; voice whenever in a car.

Is car traveling something that can be taught to a cat? There is the
possibility that I will want Marmalade to do a little weekend car traveling
with me, and I can't listen to him howl the whole time.

I have a nice little traveling &quot;kennel&quot; for him. Should I start out by
putting him in this every time I go anywhere (run to town, grocery store,
etc) and taking him with me? Our weather is very mild right now, so it
wouldn't be a problem to leave him in the car while I ran into the store.

Has anyone every trained a cat in this way, or is it just something that
they either hate or like?

