Yep, that was Uncle Sid with the horrible foot. The other cat was
killing his birds at the feeder, at their house. He was mighty picky
about his birds, and sat in the carport with an air rifle,
systematically picking off &quot;undesirable&quot; birds - Jays, sparrows,
anybody unfortunate enough not to be pretty. This stray cat got a
cardinal so Sid trapped the cat and hauled it off. I can't remember
just how all that happened, but he put the cat in a Safeway bag and off
they went. The cat got loose in the car and nearly killed Uncle Sid. He
was lacerated from the top of his bald head to his ankles, bleeding
like a cut hog. As I recall, he got pretty infected from it later. He
got the thing way out in the country and FINALLY got it out of the car.
Went home - stopped at the drug store or something on the way - and
there was the cat. I'll have to ask my mother the rest of it, because
we laughed about it for years.

