just horrible. It was so purple and swollen. I don't know how he ever
got to keep it. We couldn't even bear to look at it. It gagged us. I
can't imagine he didn't know that. But he kept it bare and propped up
on the recliner. He had kicked Odessa for years because she was an
ankle-biter in the morning. She hated him with a passion.

The day this thing happened, he was propped up snoozing in the
recliner. Odessa was on top of the book case. We looked up there and
she was crouched, tail twitching and eyes narrowed to slits. She AIMED
at that foot and jumped from the 6-foot bookcase.

I wish I could remember the rest of it, but I remember that we just RAN
in the other room when she landed on that poor foot.

